nt Update] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090930144944/http://www.slsa.com.au/site/_content/resource/00001709-docsource.pdf |date=30 September 2009 }}</ref><ref name=\"SLSA_02\">[http://www.surflifesaving.com.au/secure/downloadfile.asp?fileid=1003250 Surf Life Saving Australia \u2013 Circular: August 2008] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120324191907/http://www.surflifesaving.com.au/secure/downloadfile.asp?fileid=1003250 |date=24 March 2012 }}</ref>\n* [[Yamaha WaveRunner]] FX High Output, [[Personal water craft|PWC]]<ref name=\"APOLA_sponsors\"/><ref name=\"WaveRunners\"/><ref name=\"SLSA_01\"/><ref name=\"SLSA_02\"/><ref>[http://www.powerboat-world.com/Yamaha-WaveRunners-On-Bondi-Rescue/58486/arc Yamaha WaveRunners On Bondi Rescue] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090710015513/http://www.powerboat-world.com/Yamaha-WaveRunners-On-Bondi-Rescue/58486/arc |date=10 July 2009 }}</ref>\n* Kracka and Bennet [[surfboard|surf rescue board]]<ref>[http://www.krackasurfcraft.com.au/index.php/Latest-News/new-kracka-designed-surf-rescue-board.html New Kracka Designed Surf Rescue Board!] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090707075400/http://www.krackasurfcraft.com.au/index.php/Latest-News/new-kracka-designed-surf-rescue-board.html |date=7 July 2009 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.krackasurfcraft.com.au/index.php/Lifeguard/lifeguard-board.html Kracka Lifeguard boards] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090707075050/http://www.krackasurfcraft.com.au/index.php/Lifeguard/lifeguard-board.html |date=7 July 2009 }}</ref>\n\n==''Bondi Rescue: Bali''==\n\nA nine-part spin-off series, entitled ''Bondi Rescue: Bali'' and set in [[Bali]], [[Indonesia]], premiered on 10 September 2008.<ref>[http://www.news.com.au/dailytelegraph/story/0,22049,23836906-5006014,00.html Channel 10 puts Logie-winning Bondi Rescue into Bali]</ref><ref name=TVT>[http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2008/06/bondi-rescue-heads-to-bali.html Bondi Rescue heads to Bali]</ref> The spin-off followed two months delegations of the Bondi lifeguards (including Dean 'Deano' Gladstone, Andrew 'Reidy' Reid, Ryan 'Whippet' Clark, Chris 'Chappo/Chips' Chapman, Tom 'Egg' Bunting, Matt 'Matty' Dee, Aaron 'Azza' and Kobi Graham and mission chief Terry 'Tezz' McDermott) as they were assigned to a two-month stint at Kuta Kuta Beach, dealing with the more humid climate, a much larger beach, an exceptionally strong surf and the absence of the rescue equipment they had back home (even in ambulances), making it the world's most deadly guarded beach: twelve fatalities in an average year.<ref name=TVT2>[http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2008/08/airdate-bondi-rescue-bali-kennys-world.html Airdate: Bondi Rescue: Bali, Kenny's World]</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bondi Rescue boys feel heat on the beach at Kuta, Bali|url=http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/entertainment/tv/new-lease-on-lifesaving/story-e6frexlr-1111117441076|publisher= [[The Daily Telegraph (Sydney)|Daily Telegraph]]|date=10 September 2008}}</ref> They join the hundred strong local life guards, supervised by popular singer Marcello Arayafaya, in an official international exchange program.\n\nThe spin-off failed to score ratings, and was cancelled after four episodes.<ref>[http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2008/10/returning-jamie-oliver-bumped-kenny-gone-bondi.html Returning: Jamie Oliver. Bumped: Kenny. Gone: Bondi]</ref> However the whole series was aired and repeated overseas, notably in Flanders.\n\n==Reception==\n\n''Bondi Rescue'' has proven to be very successful for [[Network Ten|10]], averaging 1.31&nbsp;million viewers during its third season. It won the [[Logie Awards]] Most Popular Factual Program in [[Logie Awards of 2008|2008]], [[Logie Awards of 2009|2009]], [[Logie Awards of 2010|2010]], [[Logie Awards of 2011|2011]] and [[Logie Awards of 2012|2012]] and also a nomination for the Most Outstanding Factual Series at the 2010 and 2011 ceremonies.<ref name=TVT/> Its success also led to similar series such as the [[Seven Network]]'s ''[[Surf Patrol]]'' and [[Nine Network|Nine]]'s ''Deadly Surf'' being commissioned.<ref>[http://www.smh.com.au/news/tv--radio/bondi-surf-rescue-show-goes-global/2007/01/13/1168105225838.html Bondi surf rescue show goes global]</ref>\n\n===Logie Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Nominee\n! Award\n! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| '''[[Logie Awards of 2008|2008]]'''\n| Bondi Rescue\n| Most Popular Factual Program\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Bondi Rescue\n| Most Outstanding Factual Program\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"| '''[[Logie Awards of 2009|2009]]'''\n| Bondi Rescue\n| Most Popular Factual Program\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| '''[[Logie Awards of 2010|2010]]'''\n| Bondi Rescue\n| Most Popular Factual Program\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Bondi Rescue\n| Most Outstanding Factual Program\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| '''[[Logie Awards of 2011|2011]]'''\n| Bondi Rescue\n| Most Popular Factual Program\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Bondi Rescue\n| Most Outstanding Factual Program\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"| '''[[Logie Awards of 2012|2012]]'''\n| Bondi Rescue\n| Most Popular Factual Program\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"| '''[[Logie Awards of 2013|2013]]'''\n| Bondi Rescue\n| Most Popular Factual Program\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"| '''[[Logie Awards of 2014|2014]]'''\n| Bondi Rescue\n| [[Logie Award for Most Popular Reality Program|Most Popular Reality Program]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"| '''[[Logie Awards of 2015|2015]]'''\n| Bondi Rescue\n| Most Popular Factual Program\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"| '''[[Logie Awards of 2016|2016]]'''\n| Bondi Rescue\n| Most Popular Factual Program\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"| '''[[Logie Awards of 2017|2017]]'''\n| Bondi Rescue\n| Most Popular Factual Program\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Books==\nThe first book written about ''Bondi Rescue'' was by ''Nick Carroll'' and published on 1 November 2009. It was titled ''Out the Back with Bondi Rescue: True Stories Behind the Hit TV Show'' and was about the Bondi lifeguards and took readers 'behind-the-scenes' and showed their 'journeys and the effect this has had on their lives'.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/9459217-out-the-back-with-bondi-rescue|title=Out the Back with Bondi Rescue|date=1 November 2009|last=[[Goodreads]]; [[Allen & Unwin]]|accessdate=7 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nA second book, titled ''Stories From the Bondi Lifeguards'', was published on 1 February 2015 and showed a 'behind-the-scenes' look and memorable stories from the lifeguards on ''Bondi Rescue''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/23228968-stories-from-the-bondi-lifeguards|title=Stories From the Bondi Lifeguards|date=1 February 2015|last1=[[Goodreads]]; The Bondi Boys|accessdate=7 March 2019}}</ref> The book was written by a some of the lifeguards who frequented the show.\n\n==Mobile Game==\n\nA game based on the show was developed for iPhone and iPad. In the game, the player is a lifeguard who must keep the swimmers between the flags and protect them from hazards.\n\n==Series Overview==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|- \"\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"| Originally Aired\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Episodes\n!colspan=\"3\"|DVD \n|-\n!First Aired\n!Last Aired\n!Release date\n!Discs\n!Special Features\n|-\n| 1\n| {{Start date|2006|02|06|df=y}}\n| {{End date|2006|03|27|df=y}}\n| 8\n| 13 February 2008\n| 2\n| Slipcase Packaging\n|-\n| 2\n| {{Start date|2007|02|05|df=y}}\n| {{End date|2007|04|09|df=y}}\n| 10\n| 13 February 2008\n| 2\n| Slipcase Packaging\n|-\n| 3\n| {{Start date|2008|02|05|df=y}}\n| {{End date|2008|05|06|df=y}}\n| 14\n| 17 September 2008\n| 2\n| Slipcase Packaging\n|-\n| 4\n| {{Start date|2009|02|08|df=y}}\n| {{End date|2009|05|03|df=y}}\n| 13\n| 5 August 2009\n| 2\n| Hoppo rescue\n|-\n| 5\n| {{Start date|2010|02|07|df=y}}\n| {{End date|2010|05|02|df=y}}\n| 13\n| 3 August 2011 \n| 2\n| Slipcase Packaging\n|-\n| 6\n| {{Start date|2011|02|0